Windows XP (2001)

Released: 2001, based on NT kernel

Editions: Home, Professional, Media Center, Tablet PC, x64

Stable, user-friendly interface

Start menu and taskbar layout became standard

Supported wide range of hardware and peripherals

Networking: improved home & business networking features

Security: basic at launch, improved via Service Packs

Compatible with most software and games of the era

Lightweight, runs on older PCs with limited resources

Service Packs provided key updates and security patches

Still widely used in legacy systems for compatibility testing

Professional Notes:

Reliable for legacy business applications

Supports productivity tools like Office XP

Can be run in virtual machines for testing old software

Minimal system requirements make it suitable for older hardware
